From: Apollo Linux Team <dev@apollolinux.org>
Subject: [PATCH 07/12] nvidia-390xx: fix access_ok and GPU mode switch (kernel 6.8)

Kernel 6.8 changes:

1. access_ok() no longer takes a 'type' argument (VERIFY_READ/VERIFY_WRITE
   were already removed in 5.0, but 390xx had compat ifdefs that now break).

2. nv_drm_gem_prime_get_sg_table() signature changed:
   dma_buf_ops.get_sg_table now returns dma_buf_map* instead of sg_table*.

3. NV_CLEAR_USER_PAGES macro broken due to __clear_user() signature change.

4. gpu_mode_switch path uses deprecated VM_FAULT_SIGBUS without VMA lock.

Signed-off-by: Apollo Linux Team <dev@apollolinux.org>
---
diff --git a/kernel/nvidia/nv-linux.h b/kernel/nvidia/nv-linux.h
--- a/kernel/nvidia/nv-linux.h
+++ b/kernel/nvidia/nv-linux.h
@@ -1,4 +1,16 @@
+/* access_ok: type argument removed in kernel 5.0
+   Legacy 390xx had ifdefs that still tried to pass it;
+   this removes them unconditionally for kernel 6.8+ */
+#if LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(5, 0, 0)
+#undef NV_ACCESS_OK
+#define NV_ACCESS_OK(type, addr, size) access_ok((addr), (size))
+#endif
+
+/* __clear_user replaced with clear_user in 6.8 zero-page paths */
+#if LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(6, 8, 0)
+#define NV_CLEAR_USER(addr, size) clear_user((addr), (size))
+#else
+#define NV_CLEAR_USER(addr, size) __clear_user((addr), (size))
+#endif

diff --git a/kernel/nvidia-drm/nvidia-drm-gem.c b/kernel/nvidia-drm/nvidia-drm-gem.c
--- a/kernel/nvidia-drm/nvidia-drm-gem.c
+++ b/kernel/nvidia-drm/nvidia-drm-gem.c
@@ -1,6 +1,12 @@
+#if LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(6, 8, 0)
+static struct sg_table *nv_drm_gem_prime_get_sg_table(struct drm_gem_object *gem)
+{
+    /* Wrap new API: return sg_table directly */
+    return drm_gem_map_dma_buf_sg(gem);
+}
+#endif
